{"id":"42e8b9cd69d7","text":"Reasonable substitution is the most common deviation mode: Claude swaps a specified approach for one that seems equivalent because the codebase looks authoritative","domain":"deviation.substitution","agent_source":"spec-compliance-spec","type":"best_practice","confidence":0.667,"source":"spec-compliance-system.md","embedding_idx":null,"first_seen":"2026-03-29","last_validated":"2026-03-29","status":"active","evidence":{"accepted":0,"rejected":0,"modified":0},"projects_seen":[],"tags":["deviation","substitution","codebase"],"related_claims":[]}
{"id":"538d72b289c9","text":"Additive deviation occurs when Claude adds a prop, feature, or UI element that was not specified, even when the addition is sensible in isolation","domain":"deviation.additive","agent_source":"spec-compliance-spec","type":"best_practice","confidence":0.667,"source":"spec-compliance-system.md","embedding_idx":null,"first_seen":"2026-03-29","last_validated":"2026-03-29","status":"active","evidence":{"accepted":0,"rejected":0,"modified":0},"projects_seen":[],"tags":["deviation","additive","scope_creep"],"related_claims":[]}
{"id":"0dddb1abef9e","text":"Silent omission occurs when Claude skips a spec requirement without flagging it, leaving no trace that something was missed","domain":"deviation.omission","agent_source":"spec-compliance-spec","type":"best_practice","confidence":0.667,"source":"spec-compliance-system.md","embedding_idx":null,"first_seen":"2026-03-29","last_validated":"2026-03-29","status":"active","evidence":{"accepted":0,"rejected":0,"modified":0},"projects_seen":[],"tags":["deviation","omission","silent"],"related_claims":[]}
{"id":"305c0d4c70b1","text":"Layout reinterpretation occurs when Claude changes spatial relationships because it thinks the layout works better, treating the spec placement as a suggestion","domain":"deviation.layout","agent_source":"spec-compliance-spec","type":"best_practice","confidence":0.667,"source":"spec-compliance-system.md","embedding_idx":null,"first_seen":"2026-03-29","last_validated":"2026-03-29","status":"active","evidence":{"accepted":0,"rejected":0,"modified":0},"projects_seen":[],"tags":["deviation","layout","spatial"],"related_claims":[]}
{"id":"5c30946c08a4","text":"Tool substitution occurs when Claude uses a different library or tool than the spec requires, potentially introducing behavioral differences the author anticipated","domain":"deviation.tool_substitution","agent_source":"spec-compliance-spec","type":"best_practice","confidence":0.667,"source":"spec-compliance-system.md","embedding_idx":null,"first_seen":"2026-03-29","last_validated":"2026-03-29","status":"active","evidence":{"accepted":0,"rejected":0,"modified":0},"projects_seen":[],"tags":["deviation","tool","library"],"related_claims":[]}
{"id":"10aff48874bc","text":"All five deviation modes share a root cause: descriptive language that invites interpretation","domain":"deviation","agent_source":"spec-compliance-spec","type":"architectural_rule","confidence":0.667,"source":"spec-compliance-system.md","embedding_idx":null,"first_seen":"2026-03-29","last_validated":"2026-03-29","status":"active","evidence":{"accepted":0,"rejected":0,"modified":0},"projects_seen":[],"tags":["deviation","root_cause","language"],"related_claims":[]}
{"id":"9f863573e625","text":"MUST statements must be binary: either true in the final implementation or not, with no partial compliance","domain":"format.must","agent_source":"spec-compliance-spec","type":"architectural_rule","confidence":0.667,"source":"spec-compliance-system.md","embedding_idx":null,"first_seen":"2026-03-29","last_validated":"2026-03-29","status":"active","evidence":{"accepted":0,"rejected":0,"modified":0},"projects_seen":[],"tags":["must","binary","testable"],"related_claims":[]}
{"id":"4960d42a054d","text":"Each MUST statement should name the exact CSS property, component, variable, or API with specific values","domain":"format.must","agent_source":"spec-compliance-spec","type":"best_practice","confidence":0.667,"source":"spec-compliance-system.md","embedding_idx":null,"first_seen":"2026-03-29","last_validated":"2026-03-29","status":"active","evidence":{"accepted":0,"rejected":0,"modified":0},"projects_seen":[],"tags":["must","specificity","values"],"related_claims":[]}
{"id":"0a3e9dd1aba9","text":"Never combine requirements with and in a single MUST line; use one requirement per MUST","domain":"format.must","agent_source":"spec-compliance-spec","type":"best_practice","confidence":0.667,"source":"spec-compliance-system.md","embedding_idx":null,"first_seen":"2026-03-29","last_validated":"2026-03-29","status":"active","evidence":{"accepted":0,"rejected":0,"modified":0},"projects_seen":[],"tags":["must","atomic","single"],"related_claims":[]}
{"id":"221c0f741b32","text":"MUST NOT statements prevent the five deviation modes and are prohibitions, not guidelines","domain":"format.must_not","agent_source":"spec-compliance-spec","type":"architectural_rule","confidence":0.667,"source":"spec-compliance-system.md","embedding_idx":null,"first_seen":"2026-03-29","last_validated":"2026-03-29","status":"active","evidence":{"accepted":0,"rejected":0,"modified":0},"projects_seen":[],"tags":["must_not","prohibition","deviation"],"related_claims":[]}
{"id":"37d2ed9bc2cb","text":"Every spec should include MUST NOT: Add props, parameters, or features not listed in this spec to prevent additive deviation","domain":"format.must_not","agent_source":"spec-compliance-spec","type":"best_practice","confidence":0.667,"source":"spec-compliance-system.md","embedding_idx":null,"first_seen":"2026-03-29","last_validated":"2026-03-29","status":"active","evidence":{"accepted":0,"rejected":0,"modified":0},"projects_seen":[],"tags":["must_not","additive","universal"],"related_claims":[]}
{"id":"2f2acede7457","text":"IF CONFLICT is the most important section because it addresses reasonable substitution, the most common deviation mode","domain":"format.if_conflict","agent_source":"spec-compliance-spec","type":"architectural_rule","confidence":0.667,"source":"spec-compliance-system.md","embedding_idx":null,"first_seen":"2026-03-29","last_validated":"2026-03-29","status":"active","evidence":{"accepted":0,"rejected":0,"modified":0},"projects_seen":[],"tags":["if_conflict","substitution","precedence"],"related_claims":[]}
{"id":"917d0329b27d","text":"Three standard IF CONFLICT statements belong in every spec: spec precedence, stop on constraint, implement even if disagreed","domain":"format.if_conflict","agent_source":"spec-compliance-spec","type":"best_practice","confidence":0.667,"source":"spec-compliance-system.md","embedding_idx":null,"first_seen":"2026-03-29","last_validated":"2026-03-29","status":"active","evidence":{"accepted":0,"rejected":0,"modified":0},"projects_seen":[],"tags":["if_conflict","standard","three"],"related_claims":[]}
{"id":"4ea589d52db5","text":"VERIFY statements must be executable: a command, a grep, a CSS check, or a specific visual confirmation","domain":"format.verify","agent_source":"spec-compliance-spec","type":"architectural_rule","confidence":0.667,"source":"spec-compliance-system.md","embedding_idx":null,"first_seen":"2026-03-29","last_validated":"2026-03-29","status":"active","evidence":{"accepted":0,"rejected":0,"modified":0},"projects_seen":[],"tags":["verify","executable","testable"],"related_claims":[]}
{"id":"43fc96585414","text":"Prefer CLI commands for VERIFY over screenshot confirmation: grep and build commands are more reliable than visual checks","domain":"format.verify","agent_source":"spec-compliance-spec","type":"heuristic","confidence":0.667,"source":"spec-compliance-system.md","embedding_idx":null,"first_seen":"2026-03-29","last_validated":"2026-03-29","status":"active","evidence":{"accepted":0,"rejected":0,"modified":0},"projects_seen":[],"tags":["verify","cli","reliability"],"related_claims":[]}
{"id":"ee8fd45f4a37","text":"Every MUST should have a corresponding VERIFY statement to ensure no requirement goes unchecked","domain":"format.verify","agent_source":"spec-compliance-spec","type":"best_practice","confidence":0.667,"source":"spec-compliance-system.md","embedding_idx":null,"first_seen":"2026-03-29","last_validated":"2026-03-29","status":"active","evidence":{"accepted":0,"rejected":0,"modified":0},"projects_seen":[],"tags":["verify","coverage","must"],"related_claims":[]}
{"id":"cc3141335b1b","text":"Every spec must include a SCOPE section with exhaustive file lists for both create/modify and must-not-modify paths","domain":"structure.scope","agent_source":"spec-compliance-spec","type":"architectural_rule","confidence":0.667,"source":"spec-compliance-system.md","embedding_idx":null,"first_seen":"2026-03-29","last_validated":"2026-03-29","status":"active","evidence":{"accepted":0,"rejected":0,"modified":0},"projects_seen":[],"tags":["scope","files","exhaustive"],"related_claims":[]}
{"id":"506221cbb4cb","text":"The META section with Status: LOCKED signals to the compliance protocol that this is a locked spec","domain":"structure.meta","agent_source":"spec-compliance-spec","type":"architectural_rule","confidence":0.667,"source":"spec-compliance-system.md","embedding_idx":null,"first_seen":"2026-03-29","last_validated":"2026-03-29","status":"active","evidence":{"accepted":0,"rejected":0,"modified":0},"projects_seen":[],"tags":["meta","locked","signal"],"related_claims":[]}
{"id":"2cb7264f039d","text":"Always include git diff --stat shows only files listed in SCOPE as a VERIFY to catch scope creep","domain":"structure.scope","agent_source":"spec-compliance-spec","type":"best_practice","confidence":0.667,"source":"spec-compliance-system.md","embedding_idx":null,"first_seen":"2026-03-29","last_validated":"2026-03-29","status":"active","evidence":{"accepted":0,"rejected":0,"modified":0},"projects_seen":[],"tags":["scope","git_diff","verify"],"related_claims":[]}
{"id":"9b837f4d896d","text":"Implied but unstated requirements must be surfaced and confirmed before being locked as MUST statements","domain":"process.extraction","agent_source":"spec-compliance-spec","type":"best_practice","confidence":0.667,"source":"spec-compliance-system.md","embedding_idx":null,"first_seen":"2026-03-29","last_validated":"2026-03-29","status":"active","evidence":{"accepted":0,"rejected":0,"modified":0},"projects_seen":[],"tags":["implied","confirm","extraction"],"related_claims":[]}
{"id":"1967c4643718","text":"The review pass checks six common gaps: closed scope, additive block, VERIFY coverage, token naming, conflict protocol, and scope creep detection","domain":"process.review","agent_source":"spec-compliance-spec","type":"best_practice","confidence":0.667,"source":"spec-compliance-system.md","embedding_idx":null,"first_seen":"2026-03-29","last_validated":"2026-03-29","status":"active","evidence":{"accepted":0,"rejected":0,"modified":0},"projects_seen":[],"tags":["review","gaps","checklist"],"related_claims":[]}
{"id":"186eb7e30533","text":"The CLAUDE.md compliance protocol activates automatically when a session includes a spec with MUST/MUST NOT/VERIFY patterns","domain":"protocol","agent_source":"spec-compliance-spec","type":"architectural_rule","confidence":0.667,"source":"spec-compliance-system.md","embedding_idx":null,"first_seen":"2026-03-29","last_validated":"2026-03-29","status":"active","evidence":{"accepted":0,"rejected":0,"modified":0},"projects_seen":[],"tags":["protocol","activation","automatic"],"related_claims":[]}
{"id":"f53529434cda","text":"A MUST NOT violation is equivalent to a bug and must be treated with the same severity","domain":"protocol.enforcement","agent_source":"spec-compliance-spec","type":"architectural_rule","confidence":0.667,"source":"spec-compliance-system.md","embedding_idx":null,"first_seen":"2026-03-29","last_validated":"2026-03-29","status":"active","evidence":{"accepted":0,"rejected":0,"modified":0},"projects_seen":[],"tags":["must_not","violation","bug"],"related_claims":[]}
{"id":"e66b93f0b134","text":"Deviations must be reported in a structured format (DEVIATION: / Reason: / What I did instead: / Impact: / Recommendation:) not buried in conversational text","domain":"protocol.reporting","agent_source":"spec-compliance-spec","type":"best_practice","confidence":0.667,"source":"spec-compliance-system.md","embedding_idx":null,"first_seen":"2026-03-29","last_validated":"2026-03-29","status":"active","evidence":{"accepted":0,"rejected":0,"modified":0},"projects_seen":[],"tags":["deviation","reporting","format"],"related_claims":[]}
{"id":"663d6087d771","text":"Do not proceed past a failing VERIFY: fix the failure first, and if the fix requires out-of-scope changes, report and wait for approval","domain":"protocol.enforcement","agent_source":"spec-compliance-spec","type":"best_practice","confidence":0.667,"source":"spec-compliance-system.md","embedding_idx":null,"first_seen":"2026-03-29","last_validated":"2026-03-29","status":"active","evidence":{"accepted":0,"rejected":0,"modified":0},"projects_seen":[],"tags":["verify","failure","stop"],"related_claims":[]}
